From: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 16:34:44 +1200
Subject: [PATCH] iommu/rockchip: take all DT clocks, not just aclk+iface

Diagnostics from the RK3576 NPU bring-up nailed the failure: right after
the NPU0 domain powers on (while pm-domains still has the domain clocks
enabled) the MMU DTE_ADDR registers accept writes -- the debug value
written from rockchip_pd_power() lands and reads back.  Microseconds
later rk_iommu_resume() writes DTE_ADDR_DUMMY with only "aclk" + "iface"
(ACLK_RKNN0 + HCLK_RKNN_ROOT) enabled and the write is silently dropped:
the readback still shows the debug value.  Reads work, writes need more
clocks.

The RK3576 NPU MMU sits behind additional gates (CBUF/DSU) that must be
running for register writes to land; the vendor keeps every NPU clock
enabled while the device is powered.  Switch rk_iommu to
devm_clk_bulk_get_all() so it takes whatever clocks the devicetree lists
-- identical for every existing devicetree, which all carry exactly
aclk + iface -- letting a DT with the full NPU clock set work. The NPU
MMU DT nodes with that full clock set are added separately (they are not
in mainline).

Signed-off-by: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
---
 drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c | 30 ++++++-------
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 20 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c
+++ b/drivers/iommu/rockchip-iommu.c
@@ -93,11 +93,6 @@
 	struct iommu_domain domain;
 };
 
-/* list of clocks required by IOMMU */
-static const char * const rk_iommu_clocks[] = {
-	"aclk", "iface",
-};
-
 struct rk_iommu_ops {
 	phys_addr_t (*pt_address)(u32 dte);
 	u32 (*mk_dtentries)(dma_addr_t pt_dma);
@@ -1246,25 +1241,20 @@
 	iommu->reset_disabled = device_property_read_bool(dev,
 					"rockchip,disable-mmu-reset");
 
-	iommu->num_clocks = ARRAY_SIZE(rk_iommu_clocks);
-	iommu->clocks = devm_kcalloc(iommu->dev, iommu->num_clocks,
-				     sizeof(*iommu->clocks), GFP_KERNEL);
-	if (!iommu->clocks)
-		return -ENOMEM;
-
-	for (i = 0; i < iommu->num_clocks; ++i)
-		iommu->clocks[i].id = rk_iommu_clocks[i];
-
 	/*
-	 * iommu clocks should be present for all new devices and devicetrees
-	 * but there are older devicetrees without clocks out in the wild.
-	 * So clocks as optional for the time being.
+	 * Take every clock the devicetree provides.  Most IOMMU instances
+	 * need exactly "aclk" + "iface", but e.g. the RK3576 NPU IOMMUs sit
+	 * behind additional gates (CBUF/DSU) whose clocks must be running
+	 * for register writes to land.  Clocks stay optional because there
+	 * are older devicetrees without clocks out in the wild.
 	 */
-	err = devm_clk_bulk_get(iommu->dev, iommu->num_clocks, iommu->clocks);
-	if (err == -ENOENT)
+	err = devm_clk_bulk_get_all(iommu->dev, &iommu->clocks);
+	if (err == -ENOENT || err == 0)
 		iommu->num_clocks = 0;
-	else if (err)
+	else if (err < 0)
 		return err;
+	else
+		iommu->num_clocks = err;
 
 	err = clk_bulk_prepare(iommu->num_clocks, iommu->clocks);
 	if (err)
